    <!-- ============= Introduction ============================== -->
    <sect1 id="stickynotes-introduction">
	<title>Introduction</title>
	<figure id="stickynotes-fig"> 
	    <title>&applet; Applet</title> 
	    <screenshot> 
		<mediaobject> 
		    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/stickynotes_applet.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
		    <textobject><phrase>Shows Sticky Notes applet.</phrase></textobject> 
		</mediaobject> 
	    </screenshot> 
	</figure> 
	<para>The <application>&applet;</application> applet enables you to create, view, and manage sticky-notes on your Gnome
	    Desktop. The title, contents, and dimensions of sticky notes are easily editable. All sticky notes are saved and reopened
	    in their exact postions and dimensions when the applet is restarted (e.g. when you log out and back in).</para>
	<para>To add <application>&applet;</application> to a panel, right-click on the panel, then choose 
	    <menuchoice>
		<guimenu>Add to Panel</guimenu>
		<guisubmenu>Accessories</guisubmenu>
		<guimenuitem>Sticky Notes</guimenuitem>
	    </menuchoice>.
	</para>
    </sect1>
    
    <!-- ============= Basic Usage ============================ -->
    <sect1 id="stickynotes-basic-usage"> 
	<title>Basic Usage</title>
	<sect2 id="stickynotes-applet-menu">
	    <title>Applet Menu</title>
	    <figure id="applet-menu-fig"> 
		    <title>&applet; Applet Popup Menu</title> 
	    	    <screenshot> 
			<mediaobject> 
		    	<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/applet_menu.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
		    	<textobject><phrase>Shows Sticky Notes applet popup menu.</phrase></textobject> 
		    </mediaobject> 
	    	</screenshot> 
	    </figure> 
	    <para>Right click on the applet to bring up a popup-menu. Along with the usual panel menu options, you can use this menu to:</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>New Note</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Create a new sticky note. You can also left-click the applet to create a new sticky note.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Delete All Notes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Destroy all sticky notes.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Hide All Notes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Hide all sticky notes from the desktop.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Show All Notes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Show all hidden sticky notes on the desktop.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Lock All Notes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Lock all sticky notes from editing.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Unlock All Notes</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Unlock all hidden sticky notes for editing.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Preferences...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Customize sticky notes preferences.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Help</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Access the sticky notes user manual.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>About...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Show the About window.</para>
	</sect2>
	<sect2 id="stickynotes-note-menu">
	    <title>Note Menu</title>
	    <figure id="note-menu-fig"> 
		    <title>&applet; Note Popup Menu</title> 
	    	    <screenshot> 
			<mediaobject> 
		    	<imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/note_menu.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
		    	<textobject><phrase>Shows Sticky Notes note popup menu.</phrase></textobject> 
		    </mediaobject> 
	    	</screenshot> 
	    </figure> 
	    <para>Right click on the title of a sticky note to bring up another popup-menu. You can use this menu to:</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>New Note</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Create a new sticky note.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Delete Note</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Destroy this sticky note.</para>
	    <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Edit Title</guimenuitem></menuchoice>
	    <para>Edit the title of the sticky note. You can also double-click the title of a sticky note to edit it.</para>
	</sect2>
    </sect1>

    <!-- ============= Advanced Settings ============================ -->
    <sect1 id="stickynotes-advanced-settings"> 
	<title>Advanced Settings</title>
	<figure id="preferences-fig"> 
	    <title>&applet; Applet Preferences Dialog</title> 
	    <screenshot> 
		<mediaobject> 
		    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/preferences_dialog.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
		    <textobject><phrase>Shows Sticky Notes applet preferences dialog.</phrase></textobject> 
		</mediaobject> 
	    </screenshot> 
	</figure> 
	<para>Sticky Notes allows you to customize several settings. Some can only be modified using the
	    <application>gconf-editor</application>. Look under the key <phrase>"/apps/stickynotes_applet"</phrase>. The more
	    common ones are available in a Preferences dialog, and are outlined below. More details can be obtained by accessing
	    the stickynotes_applet schema using the <application>gconf-editor</application>.</para>
	<para>To access the Preferences dialog, right-click on the panel, then choose 
	    <menuchoice>
		<guimenu>Preferences...</guimenu>
	    </menuchoice>.
	</para>
	<variablelist> 
	    <varlistentry> 
		<term>Default width</term> 
		<listitem><para>The default width of new sticky notes, in pixels.</para></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
	    <varlistentry> 
		<term>Default height</term> 
		<listitem><para>The default height of new sticky notes, in pixels.</para></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
	    <varlistentry> 
		<term>Color</term> 
		<listitem><para>The base color used to draw all sticky notes.</para></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
	    <varlistentry> 
		<term>Default click behavior</term> 
		<listitem><para>What happens when one merely clicks the applet. You can set it to create a new note, toggle
		between showing and hiding all notes, and toggle between locking and unlocking all notes.</para></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
	    <varlistentry> 
		<term>Sticky across workspaces</term> 
		<listitem><para>Whether sticky notes are visible on ALL workspaces on the desktop.</para></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
	</variablelist> 
    </sect1>

